The Education Department says the gang attacked the school on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Education Department is providing trauma counselling to learners and teachers at Lwandle Primary School in Strand where armed robbers have stormed the school. The Education Department says the gang attacked the school on Tuesday. Education MEC spokesperson Jessica Shelver said: “The incident reportedly happened around the time learners were being dismissed. Three armed robbers entered the principal’s office and demanded tablets, computers, cellphones and cash. The principal and staff members were also robbed of their personal belongings.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)